---

<BlogLayout
  title="How to Write a Leave Application Online for Free — Office, School & College"
  description="Generate a formal leave application letter for office, school, or college online for free. Fill in your details and print or save as PDF instantly. No signup."
  canonical="/blog/how-to-write-leave-application-online-free"
  date="2026-06-30"
  readTime="4 min read"
  category="Text Utilities"
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <p>Writing a formal leave application can be awkward if you have never written one before. The Leave Application Generator on TextWonder creates a properly formatted letter in seconds — just fill in a form and it writes the letter for you.</p>

  <h2>How to Generate a Leave Application</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Go to <a href="https://textwonder.com/tools/leave-application-generator">textwonder.com/tools/leave-application-generator</a></li>
    <li>Select the mode: <strong>Office</strong>, <strong>School</strong>, or <strong>College</strong>.</li>
    <li>Fill in your name, designation (or class), recipient's name, and organisation.</li>
    <li>Set the leave from and to dates.</li>
    <li>Choose leave type: Sick, Casual, Earned, Personal, or Custom.</li>
    <li>Add any optional additional details in the Reason field.</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Generate Letter</strong>.</li>
    <li>Review and edit the letter if needed, then click <strong>Print / Save as PDF</strong>.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Leave Application Tips</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Keep the reason brief and factual — you do not owe a detailed medical explanation</li>
    <li>Mention that you will complete pending work before leaving or be available by phone</li>
    <li>State the exact number of days and dates clearly</li>
    <li>For sick leave, mention "on doctor's advice" if applicable</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Sample Leave Types</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Sick Leave</strong> — Illness, medical procedure, doctor's appointment</li>
    <li><strong>Casual Leave</strong> — Personal work, family event, domestic emergency</li>
    <li><strong>Earned Leave</strong> — Planned vacation using accrued leave balance</li>
    <li><strong>Personal Leave</strong> — Marriage, bereavement, or any personal matter</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="my-8 p-5 bg-violet-950/30 border border-violet-700/40 rounded-xl text-center">
    <p class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">Generate Leave Application Free</p>
